#. <section class="sutta" id="an9.12"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an9.12:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 9"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 9"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an9.12:0.2"
msgid "2. Sīhanādavagga"
msgstr "2. The Lion’s Roar"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 12. Saupādisesasutta → sopādisesasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an9.12:0.3"
msgid "12. Saupādisesasutta"
msgstr "12. With Something Left Over"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an9.12:1.1"
msgid ""
"Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery."

msgctxt "an9.12:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya "
"sāvatthiṃ piṇḍāya pāvisi."
msgstr ""
"Then Venerable Sāriputta robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and "
"robe, entered Sāvatthī for alms."

msgctxt "an9.12:1.3"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmato sāriputtassa etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then he thought:"

msgctxt "an9.12:1.4"
msgid "“atippago kho tāva sāvatthiyaṃ piṇḍāya carituṃ, "
msgstr "“It’s too early to wander for alms in Sāvatthī. "

msgctxt "an9.12:1.5"
msgid ""
"yannūnāhaṃ yena aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ ārāmo tenupasaṅkameyyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"Why don’t I go to the monastery of the wanderers who follow other paths?”"

msgctxt "an9.12:1.6"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto yena aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ ārāmo "
"tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā tehi aññatitthiyehi paribbājakehi saddhiṃ "
"sammodi."
msgstr ""
"Then he went to the monastery of the wanderers who follow other paths, and "
"exchanged greetings with the wanderers there."

msgctxt "an9.12:1.7"
msgid "Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr ""
"When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one "
"side."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.379"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an9.12:2.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena tesaṃ aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ sannisinnānaṃ "
"sannipatitānaṃ ayamantarākathā udapādi:"
msgstr ""
"Now at that time while those wanderers who follow other paths were sitting "
"together this discussion came up among them:"

msgctxt "an9.12:2.2"
msgid ""
"“yo hi koci, āvuso, saupādiseso kālaṃ karoti, sabbo so aparimutto nirayā "
"aparimutto tiracchānayoniyā aparimutto pettivisayā aparimutto "
"apāyaduggativinipātā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Reverends, no-one who dies with something left over is exempt from hell, "
"the animal realm, or the ghost realm. They’re not exempt from places of "
"loss, bad places, the underworld.”"

msgctxt "an9.12:2.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto tesaṃ aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ bhāsitaṃ neva "
"abhinandi nappaṭikkosi."
msgstr ""
"Sāriputta neither approved nor dismissed that statement of the wanderers who "
"follow other paths."

msgctxt "an9.12:2.4"
msgid "Anabhinanditvā appaṭikkositvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkāmi:"
msgstr "He got up from his seat, thinking:"

msgctxt "an9.12:2.5"
msgid "“bhagavato santike etassa bhāsitassa atthaṃ ājānissāmī”ti."
msgstr "“I will learn the meaning of this statement from the Buddha himself.”"

msgctxt "an9.12:2.6"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto sāvatthiyaṃ piṇḍāya caritvā pacchābhattaṃ "
"piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ "
"abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā sāriputto "
"bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then Sāriputta wandered for alms in Sāvatthī. After the meal, on his return "
"from alms-round, he went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and "
"told him what had happened."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an9.12:3.1"
msgid ""
"“Idhāhaṃ, bhante, pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya sāvatthiṃ "
"piṇḍāya pāvisiṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an9.12:3.2"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, bhante, etadahosi:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an9.12:3.3"
msgid "‘atippago kho tāva sāvatthiyaṃ piṇḍāya carituṃ;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an9.12:3.4"
msgid ""
"yannūnāhaṃ yena aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ ārāmo tenupasaṅkameyyan’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an9.12:3.5"
msgid ""
"Atha kho ahaṃ, bhante, yena aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ ārāmo "
"tenupasaṅkamiṃ; upasaṅkamitvā tehi aññatitthiyehi paribbājakehi saddhiṃ "
"sammodiṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an9.12:3.6"
msgid "Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an9.12:3.7"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena tesaṃ aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ sannisinnānaṃ "
"sannipatitānaṃ ayamantarākathā udapādi:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an9.12:3.8"
msgid ""
"‘yo hi koci, āvuso, saupādiseso kālaṃ karoti, sabbo so aparimutto nirayā "
"aparimutto tiracchānayoniyā aparimutto pettivisayā aparimutto "
"apāyaduggativinipātā’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an9.12:3.9"
msgid ""
"Atha kho ahaṃ, bhante, tesaṃ aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ bhāsitaṃ neva "
"abhinandiṃ nappaṭikkosiṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an9.12:3.10"
msgid "Anabhinanditvā appaṭikkositvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkamiṃ:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an9.12:3.11"
msgid "‘bhagavato santike etassa bhāsitassa atthaṃ ājānissāmī’”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
#. VAR: ca → keci (s1-3, pts1) | te ca (mr)
#. VAR: ca → keci (s1-3, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "an9.12:4.1"
msgid ""
"“Ke ca, sāriputta, aññatitthiyā paribbājakā bālā abyattā, ke ca saupādisesaṃ "
"vā ‘saupādiseso’ti jānissanti, anupādisesaṃ vā ‘anupādiseso’ti jānissanti."
msgstr ""
"“Sāriputta, these foolish, incompetent wanderers following other paths: who "
"are they to know whether someone has something left over or not?"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.380"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an9.12:5.1"
msgid ""
"Navayime, sāriputta, puggalā saupādisesā kālaṃ kurumānā parimuttā nirayā "
"parimuttā tiracchānayoniyā parimuttā pettivisayā parimuttā "
"apāyaduggativinipātā."
msgstr ""
"There are these nine people who, dying with something left over, are exempt "
"from hell, the animal realm, and the ghost realm. They’re exempt from places "
"of loss, bad places, the underworld."

msgctxt "an9.12:5.2"
msgid "Katame nava?"
msgstr "What nine?"

msgctxt "an9.12:5.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, sāriputta, ekacco puggalo sīlesu paripūrakārī hoti, samādhismiṃ "
"paripūrakārī, paññāya mattaso kārī."
msgstr ""
"There’s a person who has fulfilled ethics and immersion, but has limited "
"wisdom."

msgctxt "an9.12:5.4"
msgid ""
"So pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā antarāparinibbāyī hoti."
msgstr ""
"With the ending of the five lower fetters they’re extinguished in-between "
"one life and the next."

msgctxt "an9.12:5.5"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ, sāriputta, paṭhamo puggalo saupādiseso kālaṃ kurumāno parimutto nirayā "
"parimutto tiracchānayoniyā parimutto pettivisayā parimutto "
"apāyaduggativinipātā. (1)"
msgstr "This is the first person …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an9.12:6.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, sāriputta, idhekacco puggalo sīlesu paripūrakārī hoti, "
"samādhismiṃ paripūrakārī, paññāya mattaso kārī."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, there’s a person who has fulfilled ethics and immersion, but "
"has limited wisdom."

msgctxt "an9.12:6.2"
msgid ""
"So pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā upahaccaparinibbāyī hoti "
"… pe …"
msgstr ""
"With the ending of the five lower fetters they’re extinguished upon landing. "

msgctxt "an9.12:6.3"
msgid "asaṅkhāraparinibbāyī hoti … pe …"
msgstr ""
"With the ending of the five lower fetters they’re extinguished without extra "
"effort. … "

msgctxt "an9.12:6.4"
msgid ""
msgstr "This is the third person …"

msgctxt "an9.12:6.5"
msgid "sasaṅkhāraparinibbāyī hoti … pe …"
msgstr ""
"With the ending of the five lower fetters they’re extinguished with extra "
"effort. … "

msgctxt "an9.12:6.6"
msgid ""
msgstr "This is the fourth person …"

msgctxt "an9.12:6.7"
msgid "uddhaṃsoto hoti akaniṭṭhagāmī."
msgstr ""
"With the ending of the five lower fetters they head upstream, going to the "
"Akaniṭṭha realm."

msgctxt "an9.12:6.8"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ, sāriputta, pañcamo puggalo saupādiseso kālaṃ kurumāno parimutto nirayā "
"parimutto tiracchānayoniyā parimutto pettivisayā parimutto "
"apāyaduggativinipātā. (2–5.)"
msgstr "This is the fifth person …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an9.12:7.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, sāriputta, idhekacco puggalo sīlesu paripūrakārī hoti, "
"samādhismiṃ mattaso kārī, paññāya mattaso kārī."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, there’s a person who has fulfilled ethics, but has limited "
"immersion and wisdom."

msgctxt "an9.12:7.2"
msgid ""
"So tiṇṇaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā rāgadosamohānaṃ tanuttā sakadāgāmī hoti, "
"sakideva imaṃ lokaṃ āgantvā dukkhassantaṃ karoti."
msgstr ""
"With the ending of three fetters, and the weakening of greed, hate, and "
"delusion, they’re a once-returner. They come back to this world once only, "
"then make an end of suffering."

msgctxt "an9.12:7.3"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ, sāriputta, chaṭṭho puggalo saupādiseso kālaṃ kurumāno parimutto nirayā "
"… pe … parimutto apāyaduggativinipātā. (6)"
msgstr "This is the sixth person …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.381"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an9.12:8.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, sāriputta, idhekacco puggalo sīlesu paripūrakārī hoti, "
"samādhismiṃ mattaso kārī, paññāya mattaso kārī."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, there’s a person who has fulfilled ethics, but has limited "
"immersion and wisdom."

msgctxt "an9.12:8.2"
msgid ""
"So tiṇṇaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā ekabījī hoti, ekaṃyeva mānusakaṃ bhavaṃ "
"nibbattetvā dukkhassantaṃ karoti."
msgstr ""
"With the ending of three fetters, they’re a one-seeder. They will be reborn "
"just one time in a human existence, then make an end of suffering."

msgctxt "an9.12:8.3"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ, sāriputta, sattamo puggalo saupādiseso kālaṃ kurumāno parimutto nirayā "
"… pe … parimutto apāyaduggativinipātā. (7)"
msgstr "This is the seventh person …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "an9.12:9.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, sāriputta, idhekacco puggalo sīlesu paripūrakārī hoti, "
"samādhismiṃ mattaso kārī, paññāya mattaso kārī."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, there’s a person who has fulfilled ethics, but has limited "
"immersion and wisdom."

msgctxt "an9.12:9.2"
msgid ""
"So tiṇṇaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā kolaṅkolo hoti, dve vā tīṇi vā kulāni "
"sandhāvitvā saṃsaritvā dukkhassantaṃ karoti."
msgstr ""
"With the ending of three fetters, they go family to family. They will "
"transmigrate between two or three families and then make an end of suffering."

msgctxt "an9.12:9.3"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ, sāriputta, aṭṭhamo puggalo saupādiseso kālaṃ kurumāno parimutto nirayā "
"… pe … parimutto apāyaduggativinipātā. (8)"
msgstr "This is the eighth person …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "an9.12:10.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, sāriputta, idhekacco puggalo sīlesu paripūrakārī hoti, "
"samādhismiṃ mattaso kārī, paññāya mattaso kārī."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, there’s a person who has fulfilled ethics, but has limited "
"immersion and wisdom."

msgctxt "an9.12:10.2"
msgid ""
"So tiṇṇaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā sattakkhattuparamo hoti, "
"sattakkhattuparamaṃ deve ca manusse ca sandhāvitvā saṃsaritvā dukkhassantaṃ "
"karoti."
msgstr ""
"With the ending of three fetters, they have at most seven rebirths. They "
"will transmigrate at most seven times among gods and humans and then make an "
"end of suffering."

msgctxt "an9.12:10.3"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ, sāriputta, navamo puggalo saupādiseso kālaṃ kurumāno parimutto nirayā "
"parimutto tiracchānayoniyā parimutto pettivisayā parimutto "
"apāyaduggativinipātā. (9)"
msgstr "This is the ninth person …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.382"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
#. VAR: saupādisesaṃ vā ‘saupādiseso’ti → sopādisesoti (bj)
msgctxt "an9.12:11.1"
msgid ""
"Ke ca, sāriputta, aññatitthiyā paribbājakā bālā abyattā, ke ca saupādisesaṃ "
"vā ‘saupādiseso’ti jānissanti, anupādisesaṃ vā ‘anupādiseso’ti jānissanti."
msgstr ""
"These foolish, incompetent wanderers following other paths: who are they to "
"know whether someone has something left over or not?"

msgctxt "an9.12:11.2"
msgid ""
"Ime kho, sāriputta, nava puggalā saupādisesā kālaṃ kurumānā parimuttā nirayā "
"parimuttā tiracchānayoniyā parimuttā pettivisayā parimuttā "
"apāyaduggativinipātā."
msgstr ""
"These are the nine people who, dying with something left over, are exempt "
"from hell, the animal realm, and the ghost realm. They’re exempt from places "
"of loss, bad places, the underworld."

msgctxt "an9.12:11.3"
msgid ""
"Na tāvāyaṃ, sāriputta, dhammapariyāyo paṭibhāsi bhikkhūnaṃ bhikkhunīnaṃ "
"upāsakānaṃ upāsikānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Up until now, Sāriputta, I have not felt the need to give this exposition of "
"the teaching to the monks, nuns, laymen, and laywomen."

msgctxt "an9.12:11.4"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "an9.12:11.5"
msgid "Māyimaṃ dhammapariyāyaṃ sutvā pamādaṃ āhariṃsūti."
msgstr "For I didn’t want those who heard it to introduce negligence."

#. VAR: Api ca mayā → api cāyaṃ (?)
msgctxt "an9.12:11.6"
msgid "Api ca mayā, sāriputta, dhammapariyāyo pañhādhippāyena bhāsito”ti."
msgstr "However, I have spoken it in order to answer your question.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an9.12:11.7"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
